ORLANDO Pirates have revealed contract details of their latest signing Ghabadinho Mhango who joined them last week from Bidvest Wits. The Malawian player has signed a three-year deal with the Soweto giants and he joined his new teammates for a training camp in Rustenburg on Thursday the club confirmed. In a statement on their website, Pirates said: “Orlando Pirates Football Club can now confirm the signing of Malawian international Gabadinho Mhango from Bidvest Wits. "Mhango has joined the rest of his new teammates on camp in Rustenburg.“The 26-year old has penned a three year deal with the Buccaneers.The player was also quoted on the Pirates website: “I am happy to have joined this wonderful club and I look forward to the season ahead.”